ailed to parse transcript for prompt extraction\", \"error\", err)\n        return \"\"\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 6: `AbsPath` failure silently falls back to relative path\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 149-152\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:** When `paths.AbsPath` fails, the code silently falls back to using the relative `sessionDir` as `sessionDirAbs`. This is misleading because the variable is named `sessionDirAbs` but may contain a relative path. Subsequent operations (`os.MkdirAll`, `filepath.Join`) will use CWD-relative paths, which could create directories in the wrong location.\n\n```go\nsessionDirAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir)\nif err != nil {\n    sessionDirAbs = sessionDir  // silently use relative path\n}\n```\n\n**Hidden Errors:** Any error from `AbsPath` (missing git common dir, etc.).\n\n**User Impact:** Session metadata could be written to the wrong directory. The user sees success but the checkpoint data is in an unexpected location and may not be found later.\n\n**Recommendation:** This should be a hard error, not a silent fallback:\n\n```go\nsessionDirAbs, err := paths.AbsPath(ctx, sessionDir)\nif err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to resolve session directory path: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 7: `strategy.EnsureSetup` failure is silently swallowed\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 143-145\n\n**Severity:** HIGH\n\n**Issue Description:** If `strategy.EnsureSetup` fails, the code logs a warning and continues. But `EnsureSetup` presumably sets up the strategy infrastructure needed for `SaveStep` and `CondenseSessionByID` to work. If setup fails, subsequent operations will likely fail too, but with confusing errors that do not point back to the root cause (missing setup).\n\n```go\nif err := strategy.EnsureSetup(ctx); err != nil {\n    logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to ensure strategy setup\")\n}\n```\n\nNote the error value is not included in the log message either.\n\n**User Impact:** The user hits a cascade of confusing errors from `SaveStep` or `CondenseSessionByID`, when the real problem was that strategy setup failed.\n\n**Recommendation:** Either return the error (preferred) or at minimum include the error value in the log:\n\n```go\nif err := strategy.EnsureSetup(ctx); err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to set up strategy: %w\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 8: `DetectFileChanges` failure is silently downgraded\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 125-128\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:** If `DetectFileChanges` fails, the code logs a warning (without the error value) and continues with `changes == nil`. This means the checkpoint will only contain transcript-extracted files, missing any actual git status changes. The user is told \"Checkpoint saved (transcript only, no uncommitted file changes detected)\" which is misleading -- it is not that no changes were detected, it is that detection failed.\n\n**User Impact:** The user thinks there are no uncommitted changes when in reality the detection failed. The checkpoint may be incomplete.\n\n**Recommendation:** Include the error in the log and consider whether this should be a hard failure or at least a user-visible warning:\n\n```go\nchanges, err := DetectFileChanges(ctx, nil)\nif err != nil {\n    logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to detect file changes, checkpoint may be incomplete\", \"error\", err)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 9: Missing error value in `logging.Warn` calls throughout\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 118, 127, 144, 238, 249, 252\n\n**Severity:** HIGH (cumulative)\n\n**Issue Description:** Six `logging.Warn` calls omit the actual error value. The log messages describe what failed but provide zero diagnostic information about *why*. Compare line 225 which correctly includes `\"error\", err` with lines 118, 127, 144, 238, 249, and 252 which do not.\n\n**Affected lines:**\n- Line 118: `logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to extract modified files from transcript\")` -- missing `\"error\", fileErr`\n- Line 127: `logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to detect file changes\")` -- missing `\"error\", err`\n- Line 144: `logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to ensure strategy setup\")` -- missing `\"error\", err`\n- Line 238: `logging.Warn(ctx, \"failed to condense session — checkpoint saved on shadow branch only\")` -- missing `\"error\", err`\n- Line 249: `logging.Warn(ctx, \"failed to transition session to idle\")` -- missing `\"error\", transErr`\n- Line 252: `logging.Warn(ctx, \"failed to save session state after transition\")` -- missing `\"error\", saveErr`\n\n**User Impact:** When debugging issues in production, the log files will show *that* something failed but not *why*. This makes debugging significantly harder, especially for the condensation and session state errors which are already silently swallowed.\n\n**Recommendation:** Add `\"error\", <err_variable>` to every `logging.Warn` call.\n\n---\n\n### Issue 10: `state != nil` check after `LoadSessionState` succeeds without error -- silent no-op if nil\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 178-188\n\n**Severity:** MEDIUM\n\n**Issue Description:** After `InitializeSession` succeeds, the code loads the session state and checks `if state != nil`. If the session was just initialized but `LoadSessionState` returns nil (no error, but nil state), the attach-specific metadata update is silently skipped. The user gets no indication that their `CLIVersion` and `TranscriptPath` were not saved.\n\n```go\nstate, err := strategy.LoadSessionState(ctx, sessionID)\nif err != nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load session state: %w\", err)\n}\nif state != nil {  // What if state is nil here? Silent skip.\n    state.CLIVersion = versioninfo.Version\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n**User Impact:** Session metadata may be incomplete without any indication.\n\n**Recommendation:** If state is nil immediately after initialization, that is a bug and should be treated as an error:\n\n```go\nif state == nil {\n    return fmt.Errorf(\"session state not found after initialization (session_id=%s)\", sessionID)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Issue 11: `promptAmendCommit` failure shows fallback but logging.Warn omits user-facing context\n\n**Location:** `/Users/ninawork/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/attach.go`, lines 224-227\n\n**Severity:** LOW (well handled, minor improvement possible)\n\n**Issue Description:** This is actually one of the better-handled error paths. When `promptAmendCommit` fails, the error is logged and the user gets a manual fallback with the checkpoint ID. However, the user does not know *why* the amend failed. Was it a git hook? A permission issue? A detached HEAD?\n\n**Recommendation:** Print a brief reason to the user:\n\n```go\nif err := promptAmendCommit(ctx, w, checkpointIDStr, force); err != nil {\n    logging.Warn(logCtx, \"failed to amend commit\", \"error\", err)\n    fmt.Fprintf(w, \"\\nCould not amend commit automatically: %v\\n\", err)\n    fmt.Fprintf(w, \"Copy to your commit message to attach:\\n\\n  Entire-Checkpoint: %s\\n\", checkpointIDStr)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| # | Location | Severity | Issue |\n|---|----------|----------|-------|\n| 1 | attach.go:99-103 | HIGH | Silent transcript search fallback discards errors |\n| 2 | transcript.go:43-66 | HIGH | Fallback search hardcoded to Claude Code only |\n| 3 | attach.go:99,104 | MEDIUM | `os.Stat` only checks `IsNotExist`, ignores other errors |\n| 4 | attach.go:235-257 | CRITICAL | `condenseAndFinalizeSession` swallows 4 errors silently |\n| 5 | attach.go:321-335 | MEDIUM | Transcript parse failure returns empty string with no logging |\n| 6 | attach.go:149-152 | MEDIUM | `AbsPath` failure silently falls back to relative path |\n| 7 | attach.go:143-145 | HIGH | `EnsureSetup` failure swallowed, causes cascading errors |\n| 8 | attach.go:125-128 | MEDIUM | `DetectFileChanges` failure misleads user about changes |\n| 9 | attach.go (6 lines) | HIGH | Six `logging.Warn` calls omit actual error values |\n| 10 | attach.go:178-188 | MEDIUM | Nil state after init silently skips metadata update |\n| 11 | attach.go:224-227 | LOW | Amend failure does not tell user why it failed |\n\nThe most critical fix is **Issue 4** (`condenseAndFinalizeSession`). This function is the heart of the attach operation -- it moves the checkpoint from the ephemeral shadow branch to permanent storage. When it fails silently, the user believes the attach succeeded, but their checkpoint is at risk of being lost when the shadow branch is cleaned up. The user must be informed when condensation fails.\n\nThe second priority is **Issue 9** (missing error values in logs). Every single `logging.Warn` call in this PR (except one on line 225) omits the error value. This makes production debugging nearly impossible and should be a mechanical fix across all six locations.</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>36320</total_tokens><tool_uses>10</tool_uses><duration_ms>106730</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>\nFull transcript available at: /private/tmp/claude-502/-Users-ninawork-entire-devenv-cli/043d5e84-d945-425a-8479-8fccab0a38c3/tasks/ab232152912de0a7a.output\n\n---\n\n<task-notification>\n<task-id>a6d4f79413728431c</task-id>\n<tool-use-id>REDACTED</tool-use-id>\n<output-file>/private/tmp/claude-502/-Users-ninawork-entire-devenv-cli/043d5e84-d945-425a-8479-8fccab0a38c3/tasks/a6d4f79413728431c.output</output-file>\n<status>completed</status>\n<summary>Agent \"Comment analysis PR #688\" completed</summary>\n<result>Good. The agent list matches the registry. Now let me check whether the `Long` help mentions \"cursor\" but the registry uses `cursor` -- yes both match. Let me also look at the `--agent` flag help text which duplicates th